SIMPLE: sea_trumpet
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sea trumpet
<hw>Sea" trum"pet</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>A great blackish seaweed of the Southern Ocean, having a hollow and
expanding stem and a pinnate frond, sometimes twenty feet
long.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Any large marine univalve shell
of the genus Triton. See <er>Triton</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sea turn</ent>⟦br⟧
